The c7 pawn stopped by two white pieces! Also the e6 bishop hasn't got any
outlets.} 20... Qd7 21. Bxd6 21... cxd6 $5 ({After} 21... Qxd6 {Black has a
big problem with his backward pawn. But now White receives an "eternal" square
for his knight.}) 22. Nd4 Re5 23. Rc3 b4 24. Rg3 $1 {It is redundant on the
c-file now, so the rook comes nearer to the opponent's king...} 24... a5 25.
Kh2 Bf7 26. Nf3 Rf5 27. Qd4 27... g6 {Of course Black didn't want to weaken
his black squares more, but what else to do? After} (27... Be6 28. Re1 Re8 29.
Qb6 $5 {it's very difficult to "hold" all his pawns.}) 28. Qd2 Re8 29. Nd4
29... Rfe5 $1 {  A sign for storm.} 30. f4 Re4 31. f5 Kh8 (31... Qa7 $5) 32.
Qh6 Qe7 33. Nf3 Qf8 34. Qg5 Qg7 35. f6 $1 {
